    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-06-01T14:19:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-06-01T14:19:00-05:00" n="215"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <head>215. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d215fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 330.13/6–157. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-06-01T15:19:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1957—3:19 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8429. Eyes Only for <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName>. Department
                    disturbed by reports that “22 Point Memorandum” given to <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZVA1">Zorin</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d215fn2">Reference is to the memorandum of 35, not 22,
                        points, <ref target="#d214">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> before completion of consultation with Western Powers on all
                    points in new US “Proposals” (USDEL No. 236<note n="3" xml:id="d215fn3">USDEL
                        Disarmament 236 (telegram 6623) from London, May 31, is not printed.
                        (Department of State, Central Files, 330.13/5–3157)</note> and Paris 6149
                    repeated to London as 957<note n="4" xml:id="d215fn4">For portions of telegram
                        6149 from Paris, June 1, see <ref target="#d216fn5">footnote 5, <hi
                                rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>). Department attaches utmost importance to full Western
                    consultations and requests report on circumstances in view especially
                    discussions here with British and French during your visit and President’s
                    wishes expressed in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 8177.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d215fn5">Telegram 8177 to London, May 22, does not concern
                        disarmament negotiations. Reference is probably to telegram 8377 to London,
                            <ref target="#d211">Document 211</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
